<?xml-model href="../../schemas/format.xsd" type="application/xml" schematypens="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"?>
<format xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="fOntoLexLemon" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../schemas/format.xsd" display="show">
  <titleStmt>
    <title>OntoLex-Lemon</title>
    <abbr>OntoLexLemon</abbr>
  </titleStmt>
  <keyword>serialization</keyword>
  <keyword>RDF</keyword>
  <keyword>vocabulary</keyword>
  <info type="description">
    <p>The OntoLex-Lemon format is not a single file format like XML or JSON; it is an RDF vocabulary (an ontology/data model) designed to represent lexical information (dictionaries, terminologies, etc.) in connection with ontologies and knowledge graphs.
    </p>
    <p>The two main "official" locations for the core specification are:: <a href="https://www.w3.org/community/ontolex/">Main W3C Community Group Page</a>
        and the <a href="https://ontolex.github.io/frequency-attestation-corpus-information/#:~:text=This%20document%20describes%20the%20module,W3C%20Community%20Group%20Ontology%2DLexica.">OntoLex-Lemon GitHub Repository</a>.</p>
  </info>
  <mimeType>text/turtle</mimeType>
  <mimeType>application/rdf+xml</mimeType>
  <mimeType>application/ld+json</mimeType>
  <fileExt>.ttl</fileExt>
  <fileExt>.jsonld</fileExt>
  <fileExt>.rdf</fileExt>
</format>